%% Diagram: Response/Request body lifecycle states
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Unread: Response constructed\nbody.stream available
    Unread --> Locked: getReader / pipeTo / for await
    Unread --> Cloned: response.clone\ninternal tee
    Cloned --> Unread: each branch is its own body
    Locked --> Disturbed: read to EOF\nor reader.cancel
    Locked --> Unread: reader.releaseLock\n(if not yet disturbed)
    Disturbed --> [*]: body.json / clone now throws\nTypeError "body already used"

    note right of Cloned
        tee buffers chunks for the
        slower branch -- can grow
        unboundedly if rates differ.
    end note
    note left of Disturbed
        Stream "disturbed" once read
        starts. Re-reading is forbidden
        by the Fetch spec.
    end note
